,Recommended,289930,13468362,"Posted: 20 December, 2014",all,HaloFrosty,"""Great game"", it's that simple. You start your adventure with a feeder, and every minutes you are planning in your mind which trade route to choose and where to stem your bunker with most economical price.Now you are getting more and more money, and expanding your fleet with regional traders, and eventually going up to those beatiful ladies - PPMX, NPMX and Ultra-Large Container Vessel. Oh! Now you are ready for a round-the-world service. Further to ocean trading, you can always berth / unberth the vessel on your own, and I would say this is the most interesting element of this game.The difficulties...well, I guess it's hard to name your ships. With the fleet getting ever larger, I decide to simply pick a real world Liner Operator and name all my ships as per their's.As I said, it's a great game. But there are always ways to further enhance the gaming experience:-1. Canal passage. It would be great if I have to pay my canal due for passage,  sail my ship through the Suez, or may be have to anchor my ship off Cristobal a day or two due to canal congestion.2. Larger scale of map when docking/undocking my ship. It's quite often I find it difficult to expect where will I berth my lady until I see it. And if possible, it would be great to have a ""longer"" sailing option before berthing/after unberthing.3. Some more ""small contracts"" - I find it hard to believe I am shipping some thousands TEU of Radioactive Materials to Hong Kong, or loads of weapons ex. US/Canada to Cuba...4. More realistic color of the Equipments (i.e. containers) - The Equipments are just too sharp and colorful.5. Players can draw the company logo in-game, and decide where to put the Operator's Color on the ship's hull.6. More real world events - e.g.: Pay for ice-breaker when approaching Gulf of St. Lawrence, stowaways sneaked onboard at West/South African countries, economic changes that affect the global bunker price SERIOUSLY...etc.The trading mode is realistic only if the game is for General Cargo Carriers. For Container vessels, it appears more ""real world"" if we are to plan and maintain service routes across the globe...well may be it's just me thinking of this only.If you like ships, go for it. If you like trading game, go for it. If you want to sail a vessel, go for it. There's no much choice where you can sail vessels from a 480TEU feeder to a ULCV with bow/stern thrusters."
