76561197998315864,Recommended,289930,12237937,"Posted: 25 September, 2014",all,michaeljpounds,"I don't normally post  reviews, but I felt this title worth a mention.  There have been a lot of half-hearted continental simulations released recently and this definately doesn't fall in to that category!Ok, graphically, the ""driving sim"" aspect of this title could be better... It's a little 2D feeling and has a tendancy to stutter when you go for maximum speed, but it's passable most of the time.Having said that, this is, in my option, a solid micro-management sim.  You have good control over the day-to-day running of your shipping company, but can also comfortably out-source many of the more mundane tasks (albeit at a sigificant cost).Personally, I'm ok with that... I think it should be a significant expense in the early days to outsource any substantial portion of your management role in these kind of titles.After 6 and a half hours (or so) of play I can tell you the following:POSITIVES:* Storyline is ok, driven by solid tutorials... They are progressive and detailed enough to point you in the right direction without being condecending.* Graphics are better than anything else I have come across in this specific genre.* Controls are pretty instictive and as expected - camera controlled from mouse and helful auto-centering.* Sound - I've seen some negative postings, but, in general, I've been pretty impressed.  Music gets a little repetative in the world view as you spend a lot of time there, but each port is individualised and, overall, it's a pretty calming, uninvasive soundtrack.* Overall gameplay is going to keep genre fans entertained for some time... There's certainly enough variables to grab attention, but cost and development route are inevitable and welcome challenges!NEGATIVES:* It seemed to take an excessive amount of time to pass the first few story objectives. I imagine this is because this is many designed to be a ""sandbox"" title, but I'm hoping greater structure will be added in time.* On the subject of additions, the are many noteworthy european shipping ports which are currently missing... Let's hope this is remedied in any future updates!!!All in all, a worthwhile spend... Enjoy!!!!!!"
