,Recommended,289930,13744069,"Posted: 31 December, 2014",all,Wardogus,"TransOcean is a pretty cool and fun game where you just run your own maritime shipping company and you can run as many ships that you can afford. The ships range from a tiny freighter to a Panamax to a UCLV (a really big ship) and you can ship goods from ore to counterfeit goods to weapons to and from countries in the world.Gameplay wise, it's pretty simple and there is a mini game where you can dock and cast off. It does get repetitive after a while but if you play the game in bursts, it's fun. There are challenges where you can accept company contracts to ship a certain number of goods from one port to another in a certain time frame, which is rewarding in the end. There are also random events that pop up where you decide to avoid it or go through it, as well as customs checks from time to time (often on Hard difficulty). One neat feature I love about the game is there is online connectivity where players who play this game effect prices of goods if a port is visited often.However, what I do find is that when you start expanding, the amount of ships that you have to manage gets overwhelming and I wish there was a way to easily load your freighters at multiple ports.Overall, I do recommend this game but remember to play it in bursts or it will get repeititive. Score wise, about a 8/10."
76561198031013164,Recommended,289930,13758231,"Posted: 1 January, 2015",all,Sad and Boujee,"Totally addictive - after 40 hours of playing, I'm still returning to try and get those goods to Dubai on time.The game starts well, introducing you to small loads and quick trips. You don't realise it expanding around you as Northern Europe sends goods to the Mediterranean and North Africa. And then you're sending goods to America on bigger and bigger ships. Just when you think you're safe, the Investor comes and takes her cut and suddenly you're scrabbling for money. Do you risk taken the dubious goods for the Don? Of course you do, you're desparate for income and here comes the Customs to catch and fine you...It's more challenging than it seems and building your shipping line is more satisfying than you'd think. It's the exact example of powerful gameplay over expensive graphics."
