76561198047142445,Not Recommended,289930,13710270,"Posted: 30 December, 2014",all,Dr. Robot,"The base of the game is really well done. The ports, the menu, the controls and the map are all great but the game heavily suffers from lack of depth. After one playthrough of the campaign you are pretty much done with the whole game. And even within that it gets repetitive fast. There is no way to build your shipping company differntly in the next playthrough, it's always the same: load ship with goods, sell goods, fuel and repair the ship - repeat - buy more ships. No crew, port or storage management at all. You just ship goods to make money to buy more ships to transport more goods. Maybe it would be fun if there was any type of endgame like buying out the competition (there is none), buying whole ports or investing in research.One would think it gets more interesting when your company grows bigger but it only gets more tiring because there is no automation at all. You have to click everything manually for every single ship every time and you don't even have to think about it because it's too easy. The visualized ports are great but you only see them while docking manually which is fun at first but also gets old really fast.I can't really recommend this game. I would maybe recommend it for $5 since you will roughly get 5-10 hours out of the game. $20 is way too much."
