76561198017297147,Not Recommended,289930,15334836,"Posted: 13 April, 2015",all,GunnyMarx,"Heavy on pretty looks, feather-light on gameplay.So, Thumbs up for the pretty graphics of the docking-minigame.Everything else can be summarized in a few words:Tedious gameplay, very-very shallow realism, virtually non-existent long-term motivation, and full of inaccuracies.. Also I find the amount of highly unrealistic and extremely repetitive micro-management very boring. A true motivation killer.All this is played through a ""management"" interface, which does not assist one jot in managing a multi-vessel fleet. On the contrary.This game should be tagged ""shallow simulation of a shallow trade-simulation"". The docking-minigame likewise cannot be called a simulation, as is has nothing in common with handling a large vessel...in fact, not even of that of a 30ft sailboat. However, without it, this game would not even have the pretty graphics.Nice for an average 12 year old.Most definitely not a title for enthusiats of trade and management sims. If you are looking for an interlectual challenge and some insights into the ""real"" world of cargo shipping, and big scale logistics, look elsewhere.The proposed features for the announced version 2 of this title, do not seem to address these issues. Rather, it seems to take the existing version and expands it into a multiplayer version. A great pity, because the idea is great. There is no in-depth simulation of this genre to my knowledge...and there still isn't...and by the looks of it, version 2 won't change that.In my opinion, the trading and management functions and interfaces require extensive improvements, before this title deserves to be called an exciting game and a simulation.I give 10 out of 10 for the idea, and a 5 out of 10 for execution.All in all, in my view, yet another disappointment, and most definitely not worth the cost. There are more enjoyable apps in the itunes appstore."
