76561197999675599,Not Recommended,289930,25563615,"Posted: 18 September, 2016",all,Skybaxx,"TransOcean has some good points - there is a measure of strategy involved, with picking different cargoes and so on for the best profit.However, the negative aspects of the game outweigh the positive ones.Being double-charged for fuel and repair costs stands at the top of the list, in my view. When you arrive in a port, the estimated costs for fuel and any repairs are deducted from your profits for that trip. This is particularly tiresome when you arrive in a port that has expensive fuel prices, as you lose more.You still have to refuel and repair the ship though, paying for that separately.The investor you have to deal with is another aspect. Whilst she is entitled to her share of profits every quarter, the inane tasks that she forces on you from time to time are ridiculous.On at least two occasions, you are required to transport items that the feeder ships are not designed for - and if you can't complete the entire task, you face an enormous penalty. The tasks do add yet another level of strategy to the game, but they should be relevant to the ships you have at the time.Since the developers have still not seen fit to change this, or improve the game at all, then I cannot recommend TransOcean."
